content.description: Sustained and fun with a little air at the top.

Climb to the first bolt just below a dusty ledge. Become well acquainted with moist moss as you mantle upon the ledge and make your way up to a miniature cavern. A crimp and a big move take you to a fat knee bar no hands rest in Mossotopia's signature cave. Head slightly right over the lip of the cave and enjoy yourself some ledges straight up to the anchors.
content.protection: 4 bolts, Quick clip anchors at top.
content.location: Immediately to the right of Katrina. Impossible to miss because of the large cave 3/4 of the way up the route.

content.description: Climbs up the ledge then goes straight up on crimps and monos. Great movement with some tricky sequencing that requires really good route reading .
content.location: Starts in front of a dead tree on the far left side of the wall.
Between Beyond All Likelihood and Astro Zombie.

content.description: Sure to become a North Shore classic.   Start on side-pull tufas with a small sapling at face height.  Climb through friable hollow rock to the first bolt and the sandy ledge.  Continue straight up through excellent pockets and a thin edge to the tufas.  Some interesting features here including a pocket with a mono-suitcase handle.  The crux comes at the top of the tufas, making a left hand dead-point to a large pocket off of two thin slopey crimps.  Juggy pockets to the finish after that.
content.location: Dead center of the wall.  Look for the tufas halfway up.  Left of the obvious cave of Mossatopia.

content.description: Great route! Thin crimps for a couple bolts lead to crux pulls past the perma-draw. Pumpy & safe runout to the chains.
content.location: One to the right of Mosstopia

climbs.name: Fancy Feast
climbs.fa: Kareem Al Bassam and David Cardosa

content.description: Sustained and pumpy climb, with the crux around bolt 4-5.
content.location: Mossy Wall, just right of Deceptive Warmup, and the third route from the left on the wall.

content.description: Best of the three left 5.11's at this wall.  Climb up to the chossy ledge and continue on great pockets and edges through 6 bolts.
This climb has every time type of hold, which makes it very fun. Due to its immediate hard moves going into just as hard moves up top with even steeper terrain makes this a sustained route.
Bolt path and climb path don't exactly match.
content.location: Between The Ghost of Johnny Reimers and Man's Best Friend

content.description: Start at the ledge and work your way up a series of positive crimps to a decent jug so that you can  rest a bit for the committing crux past bolt 3.
content.location: Recommended stick clip as the first bolt is high above starting ledge.

content.description:
Bolt line on the arete left of Ctrl-Alt-Delete and right of Astro Zombie. 

  Decipher the tricky sequence up the arete utilizing holds on either side. Some start holds may have broken in the past and shorter climbers may require a cheater stack to reach the start holds.
fun thin climb to the right of ctrl alt delete
content.location: to the right of ctrl alt delete starts on the same ledge

content.description: In the Shade all day.  One of the longer walls at the North Shore and home to some really great 11's and 12's that climb interesting tufas and caves.  Rock quality is solid once you get above the chossy ledge at 12-15 feet.  Hopefully this ledge can be cleaned up over time.
